        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>SERVICE PROCEDURE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove engine oil pan drain plug and drain engine oil. After the oil has drained,
                    re-install oil pan drain plug and tighten to 50 Lbf-Ft (68 Nm) of torque.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 22 oil pan mounting bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove mounting bars.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove oil pan and gasket from crankcase.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Manually remove all oil pan gasket and RTV residue from both the oil pan and crankcase
                    using a hand gasket scraper. Do not use an abrasive pad or a wire wheel as stated in the service
                    manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent possible oil contamination and/or leaks, thoroughly clean all gasket and RTV
                        residue and any other debris from the interior surfaces of the oil pan prior to reassembly.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using a 10-mm wrench on the pick up tube support bolt head and a 13-mm socket on the
                    nut, tighten the nut to 17 Lbf-Ft (23 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply a 6 mm (1/4 in.) bead of RTV to the locations shown in Figures 1 and 2:</para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Where the crankcase and rear half of the front cover and the crankcase and rear oil
                        seal carrier contact each other.
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Also apply a circle of RTV around the cupped plug crankcase orientation holes
                        located on the oil pan rails of the crankcase.
                    </para>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>DO NOT apply RTV more than 5 minutes before installing the oil pan.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0191401" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0191401.png" type="png" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Applying RTV To Crankcase (Bottom View)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. CRANKCASE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TO EDGE OF SEAL CARRIER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SEAL CARRIER</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. FRONT COVER REAR HALF</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f0191402" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g0191402.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="392px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Applying RTV To Crankcase Rails</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the oil pan gasket onto the oil pan so that the edge marked FRONT is facing the
                    front cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the oil pan onto the crankcase. Place the two oil pan mounting bars on the pan
                    oil rail and install the fourteen (14) long mounting bolts finger tight.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the eight (8) shorter bolts finger tight to attach the oil pan to the front
                    cover and rear oil seal carrier.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque all oil pan bolts to 17 Lbf.-Ft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the oil dipstick.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the engine with new engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install oil dipstick, check for the proper oil level and adjust as needed.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Start engine and check for oil leaks.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
